    <item>
      <title>The Unyielding Wrath of Krodhishva</title>
      <description>Today&apos;s story will change how you see everything... In the kingdom of Panchala, there lived a young prince named Krodhishva, known for his unyielding rage. He was the master of the deadly Nagastra, a powerful missile that could annihilate entire armies. But when the great warrior Bhishma, the eighth reincarnation of Vishnu, was defeated by the Pandavas, Krodhishva&apos;s wrath knew no bounds. He vowed to reclaim the kingdom and slay the Pandavas. His anger consumed him, clouding his judgment. The once-respected prince became a ruthless tyrant, feared by all. The Nagastra, once a tool for justice, became a symbol of his unrelenting wrath. His kingdom was plunged into chaos, and his people suffered. The gods themselves wept for the downfall of Panchala. This is Wrath — the unyielding desire for vengeance that destroys everything in its path. Today we live in a world where anger and hatred are mere clicks away. Ask yourself, how close is your wrath to unleashing its full fury?</description>
